    "body": "<!-- Thank you for your contribution! We appreciate it. The following guidelines will help improve your pull request and facilitate feedback. If anything is unclear, don't hesitate to submit your pull request and ask the maintainers for assistance. -->\r\n\r\n## Motivation\r\n\r\n<!-- Explain the purpose of this PR and the goals it aims to achieve. -->\r\nWhen benchmarking DeepSeek-V3‘s prefilling stage with DP + EP under large batchsize and seqlen, the tensor size will exceed the range of int32_t, then illegal memory access occurs on fp8_quant cuda kernel and triton kernel.\r\n\r\nError reproduction:\r\n   Running Deepseek-v3 with DP32+EP32(4 H20x8 nodes), batch=128(batch=4 on each dp rank), seqlen=8192.\r\n```bash\r\n# launch server\r\nexport NCCL_IB_GID_INDEX=3\r\nthis_rank=1\r\ninit_addr=172.0.0.1:20000\r\npython3 -m sglang.launch_server --model-path /mnt1/DeepSeek-V3 \\\r\n        --trust-remote-code  --tensor-parallel-size 32  --dp-size 32 \\\r\n        --enable-dp-attention \\\r\n        --enable-ep-moe  --enable-deepep-moe --deepep-mode normal --disable-cuda-graph \\\r\n        --dist-init-addr ${init_addr} --nnodes 4 --node-rank ${rank}  \\\r\n        --host 0.0.0.0 --port 30000 --mem-fraction-static 0.4 \\\r\n        --chunked-prefill-size -1 --moe-dense-tp-size 1 \\\r\n        --disable-radix-cache\r\n\r\n# client\r\npython3 -m sglang.bench_serving --backend sglang  \\\r\n  --model  /mnt1/DeepSeek-V3   \\\r\n  --port 30000 \\\r\n  --dataset-name random \\\r\n  --random-input 8192 \\\r\n  --random-output 1 \\\r\n  --random-range-ratio 1.0 \\\r\n  --dataset-path /mnt1/ShareGPT_V3_unfiltered_cleaned_split/ShareGPT_V3_unfiltered_cleaned_split.json \\\r\n  --num-prompts 128\r\n```\r\n\r\n\r\nError:\r\n```bash\r\n  File \"/mnt1/lake/cloud/sglang-dev/sglang/python/sglang/srt/managers/tp_worker_overlap_thread.py\", line 112, in forward_thread_func\r\n    self.forward_thread_func_()\r\n  File \"/usr/local/lib/python3.10/dist-packages/torch/utils/_contextlib.py\", line 116, in decorate_context\r\n    return func(*args, **kwargs)\r\n  File \"/mnt1/lake/cloud/sglang-dev/sglang/python/sglang/srt/managers/tp_worker_overlap_thread.py\", line 143, in forward_thread_func_\r\n    logits_output, next_token_ids = self.worker.forward_batch_generation(\r\n  File \"/mnt1/lake/cloud/sglang-dev/sglang/python/sglang/srt/managers/tp_worker.py\", line 176, in forward_batch_generation\r\n    logits_output = self.model_runner.forward(forward_batch)\r\n  File \"/mnt1/lake/cloud/sglang-dev/sglang/python/sglang/srt/model_executor/model_runner.py\", line 1029, in forward\r\n    return self.forward_extend(\r\n  File \"/mnt1/lake/cloud/sglang-dev/sglang/python/sglang/srt/model_executor/model_runner.py\", line 990, in forward_extend\r\n    return self.model.forward(\r\n  File \"/usr/local/lib/python3.10/dist-packages/torch/utils/_contextlib.py\", line 116, in decorate_context\r\n    return func(*args, **kwargs)\r\n  File \"/mnt1/lake/cloud/sglang-dev/sglang/python/sglang/srt/models/deepseek_v2.py\", line 1426, in forward\r\n    hidden_states = self.model(input_ids, positions, forward_batch, input_embeds)\r\n  File \"/usr/local/lib/python3.10/dist-packages/torch/nn/modules/module.py\", line 1736, in _wrapped_call_impl\r\n    return self._call_impl(*args, **kwargs)\r\n  File \"/usr/local/lib/python3.10/dist-packages/torch/nn/modules/module.py\", line 1747, in _call_impl\r\n    return forward_call(*args, **kwargs)\r\n  File \"/mnt1/lake/cloud/sglang-dev/sglang/python/sglang/srt/models/deepseek_v2.py\", line 1359, in forward\r\n    hidden_states, residual = layer(\r\n  File \"/usr/local/lib/python3.10/dist-packages/torch/nn/modules/module.py\", line 1736, in _wrapped_call_impl\r\n    return self._call_impl(*args, **kwargs)\r\n  File \"/usr/local/lib/python3.10/dist-packages/torch/nn/modules/module.py\", line 1747, in _call_impl\r\n    return forward_call(*args, **kwargs)\r\n  File \"/mnt1/lake/cloud/sglang-dev/sglang/python/sglang/srt/models/deepseek_v2.py\", line 1154, in forward\r\n    return self.forward_mode_mlp_input_one(\r\n  File \"/mnt1/lake/cloud/sglang-dev/sglang/python/sglang/srt/models/deepseek_v2.py\", line 1293, in forward_mode_mlp_input_one\r\n    hidden_states = self.mlp(hidden_states, forward_batch.forward_mode)\r\n  File \"/usr/local/lib/python3.10/dist-packages/torch/nn/modules/module.py\", line 1736, in _wrapped_call_impl\r\n    return self._call_impl(*args, **kwargs)\r\n  File \"/usr/local/lib/python3.10/dist-packages/torch/nn/modules/module.py\", line 1747, in _call_impl\r\n    return forward_call(*args, **kwargs)\r\n  File \"/mnt1/lake/cloud/sglang-dev/sglang/python/sglang/srt/models/deepseek_v2.py\", line 283, in forward\r\n    return self.forward_deepep(hidden_states, forward_mode)\r\n  File \"/mnt1/lake/cloud/sglang-dev/sglang/python/sglang/srt/models/deepseek_v2.py\", line 343, in forward_deepep\r\n    final_hidden_states = self.experts(\r\n  File \"/usr/local/lib/python3.10/dist-packages/torch/nn/modules/module.py\", line 1736, in _wrapped_call_impl\r\n    return self._call_impl(*args, **kwargs)\r\n  File \"/usr/local/lib/python3.10/dist-packages/torch/nn/modules/module.py\", line 1747, in _call_impl\r\n    return forward_call(*args, **kwargs)\r\n  File \"/mnt1/lake/cloud/sglang-dev/sglang/python/sglang/srt/layers/moe/ep_moe/layer.py\", line 862, in forward\r\n    return self.forward_normal(hidden_states, reorder_topk_ids, seg_indptr)\r\n  File \"/mnt1/lake/cloud/sglang-dev/sglang/python/sglang/srt/layers/moe/ep_moe/layer.py\", line 904, in forward_normal\r\n    gateup_output = self.grouped_gemm_runner(\r\n  File \"/usr/local/lib/python3.10/dist-packages/torch/nn/modules/module.py\", line 1736, in _wrapped_call_impl\r\n    return self._call_impl(*args, **kwargs)\r\n  File \"/usr/local/lib/python3.10/dist-packages/torch/nn/modules/module.py\", line 1747, in _call_impl\r\n    return forward_call(*args, **kwargs)\r\n  File \"/mnt1/lake/cloud/sglang-dev/sglang/python/sglang/srt/layers/moe/ep_moe/layer.py\", line 105, in forward\r\n    c = grouped_gemm_triton(\r\n  File \"/mnt1/lake/cloud/sglang-dev/sglang/python/sglang/srt/layers/moe/ep_moe/kernels.py\", line 674, in grouped_gemm_triton\r\n    m_num_tiles_indptr = torch.zeros(batch_size + 1, device=a.device, dtype=torch.int64)\r\nRuntimeError: CUDA error: an illegal memory access was encountered\r\n```\r\n\r\n## Modifications\r\n\r\n<!-- Describe the changes made in this PR. -->\r\nMake type promotions in fp8_quant cuda/triton kernel.\r\n\r\n## Checklist\r\n\r\n- [ ] Format your code according to the [Code Formatting with Pre-Commit](https://docs.sglang.ai/references/contribution_guide.html#code-formatting-with-pre-commit).\r\n- [ ] Add unit tests as outlined in the [Running Unit Tests](https://docs.sglang.ai/references/contribution_guide.html#running-unit-tests-adding-to-ci).\r\n- [ ] Update documentation / docstrings / example tutorials as needed, according to [Writing Documentation](https://docs.sglang.ai/references/contribution_guide.html#writing-documentation-running-docs-ci).\r\n- [ ] Provide throughput / latency benchmark results and accuracy evaluation results as needed, according to [Benchmark and Profiling](https://docs.sglang.ai/references/benchmark_and_profiling.html) and [Accuracy Results](https://docs.sglang.ai/references/accuracy_evaluation.html).\r\n- [ ] For reviewers: If you haven't made any contributions to this PR and are only assisting with merging the main branch, please remove yourself as a co-author when merging the PR.\r\n- [ ] Please feel free to join our Slack channel at https://slack.sglang.ai to discuss your PR.\r\n",
